[normal]3. [bold]What are the main challenges associated with providing better and more consistent bus and rail services [bold]to isolated communities? How can these challenges be overcome?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]3.1. 
[normal]In rel
[normal]a
[normal]tion to m
[normal]eeting 
[normal]n
[normal]eed
[normal], t
[normal]o
[normal] 
[normal]perhaps 
[normal]state the obvious, cost-efficient public transport requires significant passenger flows to provide the fares income to offset costs. Rural areas ha
[normal]ve flows which are diverse and often cannot easily be aggregated together into cost-efficient routes.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.2. 
[normal]Transport in rural areas is often characterised by d
[normal]iverse
[normal] 
[normal]demands
[normal] to 
[normal]many 
[normal]different
[normal] 
[normal]locations
[normal]. 
[normal]The
[normal] rural economy is 
[normal]often
