[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.4. 
[normal]This role has evolved as groups grow in professionalism and 
[normal]become more self-reliant, and with reduced council budgets seeking a more focussed approach to outcomes sought from funding. 
[normal]This has 
[normal]also 
[normal]included encouraging CT groups to operate local bus services under Section 22 provisions, which has happened only to 
[normal]a limited extent. 
[normal]CT tenders are often no more competitive than those of 
[normal]commercial
[normal] 
[normal]operators
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.5. 
[normal]Community transport tends to focus 
[normal]well on certain 
[normal]needs
[normal] in their communities, in particular the needs of
[normal] the frail elderly and disabled
[normal] – 
[normal]which
[normal] has been a key aim of groups generally
